\"from\": 2251, \"to\": 2354, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the attack, often so devastating, played tight, a condition Krikorian attributed to nerves.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cI feel like our offense was a little bit stagnant,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said attacker Jewel Roemer.\", \"from\": 2355, \"to\": 2537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2524, \"end\": 2529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewel_(supermarket)\", \"score\": 0.9995343062682239, \"rank\": 0.0004508665696950488, \"text\": \"Jewel\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewel_(supermarket)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jewel_(supermarket)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cAnd we didn\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099t really convert on a lot of our six-on-five opportunities, which we take advantage of most other games.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Australia tied the game at eight with 2:54 left in the fourth period, and goalie Ashleigh Johnson managed to keep it there as the clock expired.\", \"from\": 2538, \"to\": 2808, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2664, \"end\": 2673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9647599654605631, \"rank\": 0.02528815801632103, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2761, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Ashleigh Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ashleigh_Johnson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Aussies and the Americans traded successful penalty shots until, on the U.S.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s sixth attempt, Australia goalie Gabriella Palm got a hand on Musselman\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s shot.\", \"from\": 2809, \"to\": 2974, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2909, \"end\": 2918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"score\": 0.9647599654605631, \"rank\": 0.02528815801632103, \"text\": \"Australia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Australia_women's_national_soccer_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2926, \"end\": 2940, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriella_Palm\", \"score\": 0.999999790989954, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabriella Palm\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriella_Palm\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabriella_Palm\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Australians went nuts.\", \"from\": 2975, \"to\": 3001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Americans looked unsure what to do.\\u00c2  \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis is the first time we\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve had to feel this feeling in some time,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d said Krikorian.\\u00c2\\u00a0 He added, \\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cThis is the reality of life.\", \"from\": 3002, \"to\": 3179, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3002, \"end\": 3015, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0044793311100239e-18, \"text\": \"The Americans\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q15416\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Americans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You do not sit on top of the podium every single time.\", \"from\": 3180, \"to\": 3234, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve made it look easy at times, but it\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s never been easy.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  This Olympic push has been among the hardest.\", \"from\": 3235, \"to\": 3348, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterthe exhaustion of a COVID-19 Olympics in Tokyo, many of the veterans considered retiring; legendary centers Aria Fischer and Melissa Seidemann did, leaving the team without much experience up the middle.\", \"from\": 3349, \"to\": 3557, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3374, \"end\": 3382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"score\": 0.9765606037988224, \"rank\": 0.02399755094336301, \"text\": \"COVID-19\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/COVID-19_pandemic\"}, {\"begin\": 3395, \"end\": 3400, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9998861561281146, \"rank\": 0.00011385546356587349, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 3462, \"end\": 3474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aria_Fischer\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Aria Fischer\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aria_Fischer\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Aria_Fischer\"}, {\"begin\": 3479, \"end\": 3496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melissa_Seidemann\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Melissa Seidemann\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melissa_Seidemann\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Melissa_Seidemann\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A condensed, three-year cycle combined with a young team has meant accelerating a lot of learning.\\u00c2  Now they will try to learn how to rebound from a loss and end the Olympics on Sunday with a win\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094and bronze\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0094against the Netherlands.\", \"from\": 3558, \"to\": 3794, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3782, \"end\": 3793, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9993292251621699, \"rank\": 0.00048331978674934087, \"text\": \"Netherlands\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Netherlands_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cWe\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099ve always talked about wanting to have the finished product on August 10,\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d Steffens said.\", \"from\": 3796, \"to\": 3895, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009cUnfortunately, you want that in the gold medal game.\", \"from\": 3896, \"to\": 3951, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But now we get another opportunity to try to show the world who we are.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Loading recommendations...\", \"from\": 3952, \"to\": 4054, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please wait while we load personalized content recommendations  Stephanie Apstein is a senior writer covering baseball and Olympic sports for Sports Illustrated, where she started as an intern in 2011 and has since covered a dozen World Series and three Olympics.\", \"from\": 4055, \"to\": 4318, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4119, \"end\": 4128, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"score\": 0.9999764580454142, \"rank\": 2.3542416058750108e-05, \"text\": \"Stephanie\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stephanie_Scully\"}, {\"begin\": 4197, \"end\": 4215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.477873231279886e-28, \"text\": \"Sports Illustrated\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sports_Illustrated\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She has twice won t